6 (2) Upon completion of the pilot program, every agency director
7 shall consider making the Healthy Employee Lifestyle Program available to the
8 agency's employees. On or before July 1, 2026, a state entity shall allow for
9 employee participation in the Healthy Employee Lifestyle Program.
10 (c)(1) At the discretion of the agency director, an employee may be
11 granted paid leave of up to three (3) days per calendar year for satisfactory
12 compliance with the Healthy Employee Lifestyle Program. The department shall
13 determine appropriate methods to reward employees who satisfactorily complete
14 the requirements of the Healthy Employee Lifestyle Program.
