16 include up to twenty-four (24) hours of leave per calendar year.
17 (2)(3) The leave granted under subdivision (c)(2) of this
18 section shall be used in the calendar year in which it was granted within six
19 (6) months of approval.
20 (3)(4) The leave granted under subdivision (c)(2) of this
21 section is not compensable at termination.
22 (d) Each agency state entity shall identify and maintain, if
23 practicable, in or near each agency building an area or areas that employees
24 may use for walking exercise.
